---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Football Data, Sponsorship & Partnerships"
  description="Download historical football tables, discuss data licensing, sponsor an archive tool or propose a relevant retail partnership."
  canonical="/partners/"
>
  <div class="container">
    <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><span class="current">Data & Partnerships</span></nav>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <h1>Data & partnerships</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Useful integrations that preserve editorial independence and reader trust.</p>
    </section>
    <div class="tool-grid section">
      <article class="tool-card"><h2>Data access</h2><p>Season-table CSV downloads are available free on individual season pages. Bulk exports and a documented API are planned after source verification.</p></article>
      <article class="tool-card"><h2>Tool sponsorship</h2><p>Relevant brands can sponsor a comparison or archive tool with restrained, clearly identified placements.</p></article>
      <article class="tool-card"><h2>Retail partnerships</h2><p>Kit retail links will only be commercialised when inventory, tracking and disclosures are accurate.</p></article>
    </div>
    <article class="prose section">
      <h2>Principles</h2>
      <ul><li>Commercial relationships do not change historical data.</li><li>Paid links are clearly identified.</li><li>No deceptive buttons, fake prices or untracked commission claims.</li><li>Gambling promotion is not currently part of the site-wide commercial model.</li></ul>
      <p>Contact <a href="mailto:partners@lastseason.co.uk">partners@lastseason.co.uk</a>.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</Base>
